<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67cd0d2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7501"><num value="7501">§ 7501.</num><heading> Duplicates</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf67cd0d3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7501/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> If a license, certificate of registry, or merchant mariner’s document issued under this part is lost as a result of a marine casualty, the holder shall be supplied with a duplicate without cost.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf67cd0d4-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7501/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> For any other loss, the holder may obtain a duplicate on payment of reasonable costs prescribed by regulation by the Secretary.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf67cd0d5-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/545">97 Stat. 545</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/36/s1/a/9/C">Pub. L. 99–36, § 1(a)(9)(C)</ref>, <date date="1985-05-15">May 15, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/68">99 Stat. 68</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/116/283/dG/tLVXXXV">Pub. L. 116–283, div. G, title LVXXXV</ref> [LXXXV], § 8505(b)(5), <date date="2021-01-01">Jan. 1, 2021</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/4751">134 Stat. 4751</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
